<figureCitation id="130C2A1CC048ED44B92EF9F19DCD206F" box="[834,941,1586,1614]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="4.[226,276,1782,1807]" captionTargetBox="[226,1353,257,1744]" captionTargetId="figure-64@4.[226,1361,249,1762]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-7: Lathrobium bucharense Koch (1-3) and L. bananum nov.sp. (4-7): (1) male sternite VII; (2, 5) male sternite VIII; (3, 6) aedeagus in lateral view (4); forebody; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 3-4, 6: 1.0 mm; 1-2, 5, 7: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518389/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="250">Figs 1-3</figureCitation>
